Title: Please do not use the .NET 2.0 HMACSHA512 and HMACSHA384 Classes
Description: We’ve recently discovered a bug in the HMACSHA512 and HMACSHA384 classes which shipped in the .NET Framework 2.0.  This bug will cause these algorithms to produce incorrect results which are not consistent with other implementations of HMAC-SHA-512 and HMAC-SHA-384.  Unfortunately, we did not discover this bug until recently, and the shipping .NET Framework 2.0 on all platforms is affected by it.  The only two affected algorithms are the HMAC-SHA-512 and HMAC-SHA-384; other HMAC algorithms do produce correct values.
